Created by Prutserdt

This is my build of dwm - dynamic window manager. An extremely fast, small, 
and dynamic window manager for X.

Check the log directory for the applied patches.
Check the config.h file for my key bindings.

My builds are made in my home direcotory (~/suckless/dwm). 
Go to that directory and enter as normal user:
make clean install

Make a symlink to ~/bin
'ln -s -v /home/icefly/suckless/dwm/dwm /home/icefly/bin/dwm'

Running dwm
-----------
Add the following line to your .xinitrc to start dwm using startx:
exec dwm

dwm patching
------------
1. Download a patch from suckless.org and place the patch at a set location 
   (~/Stack/suckless/dwm/patches/test)
2. Run from command line the .bashrc alias: dwmpatch
3. If the patch is usefull then safe as a stable version.

Safe as stable version
------------
Run from command line the .bashrc alias: dwmbackup

Restore stable version
------------
Run from command line the .bashrc alias: dwmstable

Run vanilla dwm
------------
Run from command line the .bashrc alias: dwmvanilla
